sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Trackpad
    participant Python
    participant API
    participant Service
    participant DB
    participant Govee

    Note over User,Govee: Scenario: User performs double tap to toggle light

    User->>Trackpad: Double tap (1 finger)
    Trackpad->>Python: Raw input events
    Python->>Python: Detect gesture pattern
    Python->>API: POST /gestures/execute<br/>{"gesture": "DOUBLE_TAP"}

    API->>Service: processGesture("DOUBLE_TAP")
    Service->>DB: SELECT * FROM gesture_rules<br/>WHERE gesture_name = "DOUBLE_TAP"
    DB-->>Service: GestureRule (action_id: 5)

    Service->>DB: SELECT * FROM actions WHERE id = 5
    DB-->>Service: Action (type: "LIGHT", light_action_id: 2)

    Service->>DB: SELECT * FROM light_actions WHERE id = 2
    DB-->>Service: LightAction (operation: "TOGGLE", device_id: 1)

    Service->>Govee: Toggle light command for device_id: 1
    Govee-->>Service: Success (Light toggled ON)

    Service-->>API: Execution result
    API-->>Python: 200 OK {"status": "success"}
    Python-->>User: Visual/haptic feedback (optional)

    Note over User,Govee: Light is now toggled (ON/OFF)